>has someone actually used a UHAUL AT (Auto Transport) trailer and can 
>vouch that the bus will actually fir on the trailer?

Yes, this was the trailer I used and my '64 Standard Microbus fit just
fine on it.  It came with ramps that slid out of the rear of the trailer,
webbed hold-down straps that went over the front tires, and a couple
of safety chains that went over the torsion bars.

Good luck!

Matt Roberds


